import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of Github events over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Github events per hour')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Github events per hour?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    daily_average = data.groupby('day')['count'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.bar(daily_average['day'], daily_average['count'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.axhline(y=daily_average['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-', label=f"Average: {daily_average['count'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average number of Github events per day?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    busiest_hour = data.loc[data['count'].idxmax()]['time']
    plt.axvline(busiest_hour, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Busiest Hour: {busiest_hour}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the busiest hour of the day for Github events?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
